---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/urls';
---

<BaseLayout title="Beliefs" description="Learn about Temple Aviv Judea's Messianic Jewish statement of faith, biblical foundations, and core values of Prayer, Proclamation, and People.">
  <PageHero eyebrow="Statement of faith & core values" title="One story. One Messiah. One family." intro="We embrace the Tanakh and Brit Chadashah as one continuous revelation, and Yeshua as Israel’s promised Messiah and King." accent="teal" />

  <section class="mosaic-feature mosaic-teal" aria-label="Torah artwork">
    <div class="shell mosaic-frame"><img src={withBase('/images/torah-shofar-mosaic.webp')} alt="Mosaic artwork of a Torah scroll, shofar, and tallit" width="853" height="294" /></div>
  </section>

  <section class="section belief-summary">
    <div class="shell split-layout">
      <div><span class="eyebrow">Our foundation</span><h2>Jewish roots are not a footnote. They are the context.</h2></div>
      <div class="welcome-copy"><p class="lead">Temple Aviv Judea is a Messianic Jewish congregation committed to living in accordance with Torah, the covenant between G-d and Israel, the authority of the whole Bible, and the Good News of Yeshua HaMashiach.</p><p>Jewish believers remain part of the people Israel and are called to maintain their biblical Jewish heritage. Gentile believers who feel called to this expression are welcomed as full and equal members of the community.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="live-banner-section">
    <div class="shell"><img src={withBase('/images/live/core-values-banner.webp')} alt="A Temple Aviv Judea teaching banner showing a rabbi under a tallit" width="1800" height="599" loading="lazy" /></div>
  </section>

  <section class="belief-grid-section">
    <div class="shell belief-grid">
      <article><span>01</span><h3>The Scriptures</h3><p>The Tanakh and Brit Chadashah are inspired and the supreme authority for faith and life.</p></article>
      <article><span>02</span><h3>The G-d of Israel</h3><p>There is one G-d, eternally existing as Father, Son, and Ruach HaKodesh.</p></article>
      <article><span>03</span><h3>Messiah Yeshua</h3><p>Yeshua is fully G-d and fully man, born of a virgin, crucified for sin, bodily raised, ascended, and returning as King.</p></article>
      <article><span>04</span><h3>Salvation</h3><p>We are reconciled to G-d by trusting in Yeshua’s atoning sacrifice. Our own works or merit cannot save us.</p></article>
      <article><span>05</span><h3>Ruach HaKodesh</h3><p>The Holy Spirit indwells and empowers every believer, distributing gifts for worship, witness, and service.</p></article>
      <article><span>06</span><h3>Israel & the Nations</h3><p>In Messiah, the dividing wall is broken down while Jewish identity and G-d’s covenant with Israel are honored.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pillars-section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading centered light"><span class="eyebrow eyebrow-light">The three P’s</span><h2>Values we practice together.</h2></div>
      <div class="pillars-grid">
        <article><img class="pillar-card-art" src={withBase('/images/card-blue-top.webp')} alt="" width="720" height="640" loading="lazy" /><strong>Prayer</strong><p>We praise, repent, await with expectation, and yield to the Father, Messiah, and the Ruach HaKodesh.</p></article>
        <article><img class="pillar-card-art" src={withBase('/images/card-coral-top.webp')} alt="" width="720" height="640" loading="lazy" /><strong>Proclamation</strong><p>We worship in Jewish context and lovingly share the fullness and Jewishness of Messiah. We bring this message first to Jewish people and also to the Nations.</p></article>
        <article><img class="pillar-card-art" src={withBase('/images/card-purple-top.webp')} alt="" width="720" height="640" loading="lazy" /><strong>People</strong><p>We nurture mishpachah through discipleship, shared life, spiritual gifts, acts of service, and care for our wider community.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
